Will is everything!

182
00:19:25,165 --> 00:19:26,996
反抗的意志！
The will to act.

183
00:19:36,777 --> 00:19:38,005
投降吧
Yield.

184
00:19:38,311 --> 00:19:39,710
你没有打赢我
You haven't beaten me.

185
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:42,610
为了击倒敌人 你牺牲了重心
You have sacrificed sure footing for a killing stroke.

186
00:19:50,223 --> 00:19:52,020
摩擦你的胸膛
Rub your chest.

187
00:19:52,526 --> 00:19:55,393
双手会让你变暖和
Your arms will take care of themselves.

188
00:19:58,063 --> 00:19:59,690
你比你父亲要强大
You are stronger than your father.

189
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:01,994
你不了解我父亲
You didn't know my father.

190
00:20:02,169 --> 00:20:04,467
但我知道是什么让你满腔怒火
But l know the rage that drives you.

191
00:20:04,638 --> 00:20:09,666
难以忍受的愤怒遏制了你的悲伤，直到你对所爱的人的记忆
That impossible anger strangling the grief, until the memory of your loved one is just...

192
00:20:09,843 --> 00:20:11,902
成为你心中的毒瘤
...poison in your veins.

193
00:20:12,077 --> 00:20:16,537
有一天，你会发觉自己希望你所爱的人根本从来不存在过
And one day, you catch yourself wishing the person you loved had never existed...

194
00:20:17,984 --> 00:20:20,418
这样才能减轻内心的痛苦
...so you'd be spared your pain.

195
00:20:23,456 --> 00:20:26,823
我并不是一直住在这山里的
l wasn't always here in the mountains.

196
00:20:28,428 --> 00:20:30,487
曾经，我有一个妻子
Once, l had a wife.

197
00:20:31,431 --> 00:20:33,365
我至生所爱
My great love.

198
00:20:34,534 --> 00:20:36,661
她被害了
She was taken from me.

199
00:20:36,837 --> 00:20:40,034
像你一样，我不得不明白这个世界上存在着罪恶
Like you, l was forced to learn there are those without decency...

200
00:20:40,207 --> 00:20:43,506
需要我们毫不犹豫，毫不留情的去打击
...who must be fought without hesitation, without pity.

201
00:20:45,278 --> 00:20:47,644
你的愤怒赐予你强大的力量
Your anger gives you great power.

202
00:20:48,114 --> 00:20:51,675
但如果放任不管，它会毁掉你
But if you let it, it will destroy you...

203
00:20:52,219 --> 00:20:53,447
...正如它差点毁掉我
...as it almost did me.

204
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:56,111
-是什么救了你? -复仇
-What stopped it? -Vengeance.

205
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:59,124
那对我没用
That's no help to me.

206
00:20:59,292 --> 00:21:01,157
为什么，布鲁斯?
Why, Bruce?

207
00:21:01,328 --> 00:21:03,990
为什么你不能为父母报仇?
Why could you not avenge your parents?

208
00:21:07,801 --> 00:21:11,259
少爷，你是打算听证会后返回普林斯顿大学
Will you be heading back to Princeton after the hearing, sir...

209
00:21:11,438 --> 00:21:14,100
还是听我的建议在这里逗留一两天？
...or can l persuade you to stay on for a day or two?

210
00:21:14,274 --> 00:21:16,504
我不回去了
l'm not heading back at all.

211
00:21:16,675 --> 00:21:18,700
-你不喜欢那里? -我喜欢
-You don't like it there? -l like it fine.

212
00:21:19,112 --> 00:21:21,910
只是他们不喜欢我
They just don't feel the same way.

213
00:21:22,716 --> 00:21:26,379
-我给你准备好了主卧室 -不
-l've prepared the master bedroom. -No.

214
00:21:26,553 --> 00:21:27,952
我住自己的房间就行
My room will be fine.

215
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:30,646
恕我直言，少爷，韦恩府邸就是你的家
With all due respect, sir, Wayne Manor is your house.

216
00:21:30,824 --> 00:21:32,689
不，阿福，只是我父亲的家
No, Alfred, it's my father's house.

217
00:21:32,859 --> 00:21:35,225
-你父亲过世了 -这地方是个坟墓
-Your father is dead. -This place is a mausoleum.

218
00:21:35,395 --> 00:21:38,421
如果可以，我会一砖一瓦把这地方拆干净
lf l have my way, l'll pull the damn thing down brick by brick.

219
00:21:38,598 --> 00:21:42,694
韦恩少爷，这所宅子是你家族世世代代的家
This house, Master Wayne, has sheltered six generations of your family.

220
00:21:42,869 --> 00:21:45,565
你为什么这么关心，阿福？又不是你的家
Why do you give a damn, Alfred? lt's not your family.

221
00:21:46,406 --> 00:21:50,274
我关心是因为
l give a damn because a good man once made me responsible...

222
00:21:50,944 --> 00:21:53,105
曾经有个好人，托我帮他照顾
...for what was most precious to him...

223
00:21:53,280 --> 00:21:55,510
他遗留于世上的，他最珍惜的人
...in the whole world.

224
00:21:57,484 --> 00:22:01,011
道斯小姐会载你去听证会
Miss Dawes has offered to drive you to the hearing.

225
00:22:01,187 --> 00:22:03,246
她可能会劝你不要去
She probably hopes to talk you out of going.

226
00:22:03,423 --> 00:22:06,859
阿福，我应该把我的过去和这场听证会一起埋葬吗？
Should l just bury the past out there with my parents, Alfred?

227
00:22:07,027 --> 00:22:10,121
少爷，我没资格告诉你如何处理你的过去
l wouldn't presume to tell you what to do with your past, sir.

228
00:22:10,297 --> 00:22:14,324
但我了解，有很多人想知道你会如何处理你的将来
Just know that there are those of us who care about what you do with your future.

229
00:22:15,702 --> 00:22:17,226
还是没有放弃我是吗？
Haven't given up on me yet?

230
00:22:17,904 --> 00:22:19,394
从来没有
Never.

231
00:23:07,954 --> 00:23:11,355
阿福还一直把炼奶放到架子顶上
Alfred still keeps the condensed milk on the top shelf.

232
00:23:12,225 --> 00:23:15,985
他没意识到你已经长高了. 看来是旧习难改
Hasn't he noticed you're tall enough to reach now? Old habits die hard, l guess.

233
00:23:15,996 --> 00:23:18,556
-小时候也没能阻止我们去拿 -是啊
-Never used to stop us anyway. -No, it didn't.

234
00:23:18,732 --> 00:23:20,632
你母亲怎么样?
How's your mom?

235
00:23:21,034 --> 00:23:23,264
她很想念这里
She misses this place.

236
00:23:24,771 --> 00:23:26,295
我也是
So do l.

237
00:23:26,705 --> 00:23:27,933
恩
Yeah.

238
00:23:28,108 --> 00:23:31,100
可惜物是人非
But it's nothing without the people who made it what it was.

239
00:23:31,277 --> 00:23:34,303
-阿福还在 -还有你
-Now there's only Alfred. -And you.

240
00:23:34,481 --> 00:23:38,008
-我不会久留 -你只是回来参加听证会
-l'm not staying, Rachel. -You're just back for the hearing.

241
00:23:41,621 --> 00:23:45,819
布鲁斯, 是不是没有办法阻止你去听证会
Bruce, l don't suppose there's any way to convince you not to come.

242
00:23:46,126 --> 00:23:49,618
在这过程里
Someone at this proceeding...

243
00:23:50,330 --> 00:23:52,457
总得有人去代表我的父母
...should stand for my parents.

244
00:23:52,632 --> 00:23:54,759
我们都爱你的父母
We all loved your parents, Bruce.

245
00:23:54,934 --> 00:23:58,165
-凶手吉尔做的事不可饶恕 -那为什么你的上级要放了他
-What Chill did is unforgivable. -Then why is your boss letting him go?

246
00:23:59,539 --> 00:24:02,770
在牢里, 他跟恶棍头目法康尼同住一个牢房
ln prison, he shared a cell with Carmine Falcone.

247
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:06,605
他知道些内幕, 并愿意以早释为条件, 举报法康尼
He learned things, and he will testify in exchange for early parole.

248
00:24:06,780 --> 00:24:09,442
瑞秋, 凶手杀了我父母
Rachel, this man killed my parents.

249
00:24:11,451 --> 00:24:13,180
我不能忘掉这个
l cannot let that pass.

250
00:24:13,353 --> 00:24:16,220
我也请你理解
And l need you to understand that, please.

251
00:24:17,957 --> 00:24:19,185
我理解
Okay.

252
00:24:20,260 --> 00:24:23,593
大萧条让工薪阶层遭受重创, 吉尔先生, 是个典型例子
The depression hit working people, like Mr. Chill, hardest of all.

253
00:24:23,763 --> 00:24:28,962
他所犯之罪不可饶恕,但他是由绝望所驱使, 而非贪婪
His crime was appalling, yes, but it was motivated not by greed, but by desperation.

254
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:32,070
经过14年积极的服刑
Given the 1 4 years served, as well as his extraordinary level of cooperation...

255
00:24:32,238 --> 00:24:35,769
根据我们这里最重要一位检察官的调查结果
...with one of this office's most important investigations...

256
00:24:35,909 --> 00:24:39,140
我们强烈建议批准他的早释申请
...we strongly endorse his petition for early release.

257
00:24:40,146 --> 00:24:42,444
吉尔先生?
Mr. Chill?

258
00:24:46,051 --> 00:24:47,678
法官大人
Your Honor...

259
00:24:48,588 --> 00:24:51,716
我没有一天不为自己的行为后悔
...not a day goes by that l don't wish l could take back what l did.

260
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:57,591
诚然, 和很多人一样我当时很绝望
Sure, l was desperate, like a lot of people back then...

261
00:24:57,764 --> 00:25:00,096
但这不能减轻我的所作所为
...but that don't change what l did.

262
00:25:03,702 --> 00:25:08,401
我了解今天有位韦恩家族的成员在场
l gather there is a member of the Wayne family here today.

263
00:25:08,575 --> 00:25:10,839
他有什么要说吗?
Has he got anything to say?

264
00:25:25,558 --> 00:25:28,425
-他出来了! -他出来了!
-He's coming out the side! -He's coming out the side, guys!

265
00:25:38,104 --> 00:25:39,401
布鲁斯`韦恩也在!
Bruce Wayne!

266
00:25:42,208 --> 00:25:43,436
吉尔!
Joe! Hey, Joe!

267
00:25:43,610 --> 00:25:45,077
法康尼向你问好!
Falcone says hi.

268
00:25:55,421 --> 00:25:57,013
走吧
Come on, Bruce.

269
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:59,016
我们不要看这些
We don't need to see this.

270
00:25:59,759 --> 00:26:01,317
我要看
l do.

271
00:26:06,466 --> 00:26:10,459
检察院不明白为什么法官一定要举行公开听证会
The DA couldn't understand why Judge Faden insisted on making the hearing public.

272
00:26:10,637 --> 00:26:13,037
法康尼收买了他,好让吉尔能公开露面
Falcone paid him off to get Chill out in the open.

273
00:26:13,239 --> 00:26:14,501
也许我应该感谢他
Maybe l should thank them.

274
00:26:14,673 --> 00:26:17,233
-你不是认真的 -如果我是呢,瑞秋?
-You don't mean that. -What if l do, Rachel?

275
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:19,343
我父母应该得到一个公正的结果
My parents deserved justice.

276
00:26:19,512 --> 00:26:22,413
你说的不是公正, 只是复仇
You're not talking about justice. You're talking about revenge.

277
00:26:22,582 --> 00:26:25,483
-有时候两者是一样意思 -不,从来不一样
-Sometimes, they're the same. -No, they're never the same.

278
00:26:25,652 --> 00:26:29,213
公正会带来和谐,复仇只是逞一己之快
Justice is about harmony. Revenge is about you making yourself feel better.

279
00:26:29,389 --> 00:26:32,688
-正因如此我们才会有司法系统 -你们的系统早已崩溃
-Which is why we have an impartial system. -Your system is broken.

280
00:26:39,766 --> 00:26:42,599
你如果关心公正, 就不要总局限于自己的痛苦
You care about justice? Look beyond your own pain, Bruce.

281
00:26:43,036 --> 00:26:44,503
这座城市正在腐烂
This city is rotting.

282
00:26:44,671 --> 00:26:47,435
人们觉得大萧条已经成历史, 其实没有
They talk about the depression as if it's history. lt's not.

283
00:26:47,607 --> 00:26:49,097
世道比以前更糟
Things are worse than ever here.

284
00:26:49,275 --> 00:26:51,835
法康尼让城市充满犯罪与邪恶
Falcone floods our streets with crime and drugs...

285
00:26:52,011 --> 00:26:54,946
到处是绝望, 每天都产生新的吉尔
...preying on the desperate, creating new Joe Chills every day.

286
00:26:55,114 --> 00:26:57,639
法康尼也许没有杀了你父母
Falcone may not have killed your parents, Bruce...

287
00:26:58,284 --> 00:27:00,775
但他在摧毁你父母所代表的一切
...but he's destroying everything that they stood for.

288
00:27:05,325 --> 00:27:08,226
你想感谢他? 去吧
You wanna thank him for that? Here you go.

289
00:27:10,096 --> 00:27:11,461
我们都知道他在哪里
We all know where to find him.

290
00:27:11,631 --> 00:27:14,998
只要他继续助纣为虐, 就没人敢动他
As long as he keeps the bad people rich and the good people scared, no one'll touch him.

291
00:27:15,435 --> 00:27:19,599
像你父母一样代表正义的好人, 已经一去不返
Good people like your parents, who'll stand against injustice, they're gone.

292
00:27:19,772 --> 00:27:22,673
当好人尽去, 这个城市还有什么希望?
What chance does Gotham have when the good people do nothing?

293
00:27:24,611 --> 00:27:28,047
-我不是你所说的好人, 瑞秋 -你什么意思?
-l'm not one of your good people, Rachel. -What do you mean?

294
00:27:30,283 --> 00:27:35,782
这些年来我一直想杀了他, 现在杀不了了
All these years, l wanted to kill him. Now l can't.

295
00:27:51,604 --> 00:27:53,265
你父亲会以你为耻
Your father would be ashamed of you.

296
00:28:36,749 --> 00:28:39,274
韦恩先生, 你看起来比报纸上的照片要高
You're taller than you look in the tabloids, Mr. Wayne.

297
00:28:39,718 --> 00:28:41,583
没带枪? 简直是侮辱!
No gun? l'm insulted.

298
00:28:44,757 --> 00:28:48,625
-你大可写份感谢信就行 -我不是来这里谢你的
-You could've just sent a thank-you note. -l didn't come here to thank you.

299
00:28:48,795 --> 00:28:51,491
我是来这里告诉你 不是所有人都怕你
l came to show you that not everyone in Gotham's afraid of you.

300
00:28:51,664 --> 00:28:53,291
了解我的人才怕我 孩子
Only those who know me, kid.

301
00:28:53,633 --> 00:28:56,101
看看你周围, 这里有两位参议员
Look around you. You'll see two councilmen...

302
00:28:56,436 --> 00:28:59,269
一个联邦督察 两位当值警官
...a union official, couple off-duty cops...

303
00:28:59,706 --> 00:29:01,333
一个法官
...and a judge.

304
00:29:01,507 --> 00:29:05,773
我完全可以在他们面前一枪蹦了你
Now, l wouldn't have a second's hesitation of blowing your head off in front of them.

305
00:29:05,945 --> 00:29:08,675
这样的力量你是买不到的
Now, that's power you can't buy.

306
00:29:09,315 --> 00:29:10,748
这是恐惧的力量
That's the power of fear.

307
00:29:11,184 --> 00:29:12,412
我不惧怕你
l'm not afraid of you.

308
00:29:12,585 --> 00:29:14,485
因为你觉得自己已经了无牵挂
Because you think you got nothing to lose.

309
00:29:14,654 --> 00:29:16,281
但你还没考虑仔细
But you haven't thought it through.

310
00:29:16,456 --> 00:29:19,584
你还没考虑到你那在检察院上班的女朋友
You haven't thought about your lady friend in the DA's office.

311
00:29:19,759 --> 00:29:22,193
你还没考虑到你的老管家
You haven't thought about your old butler.

312
00:29:26,332 --> 00:29:28,664
像你这样的人
People from your world...

313
00:29:28,835 --> 00:29:31,201
牵挂多的是
...have so much to lose.

314
00:29:31,371 --> 00:29:35,705
就因为你父母被害
Now, you think because your mommy and your daddy got shot...

315
00:29:35,875 --> 00:29:38,844
你就认为自己尝到了人间疾苦, 扯蛋吧
...you know about the ugly side of life, but you don't.

316
00:29:39,011 --> 00:29:41,104
你根本不知道什么是绝望
You've never tasted desperate.

317
00:29:41,280 --> 00:29:43,840
你是布鲁斯`韦恩, 歌谭市天之骄子
You're.... You're Bruce Wayne, the prince of Gotham.

318
00:29:44,016 --> 00:29:47,417
要想人们认不出你的大名, 你得远走他乡才行
You'd have to go 1 000 miles to meet someone who didn't know your name.

319
00:29:47,587 --> 00:29:51,887
所以不要怒气冲天的跑来这里, 试图证明什么
So don't come down here with your anger, trying to prove something to yourself.

320
00:29:52,057 --> 00:29:54,150
这是一个你从来不会了解的世界
This is a world you'll never understand.

321
00:29:54,326 --> 00:29:56,351
而你不了解的东西
And you always fear...

322
00:29:56,529 --> 00:29:58,963
始终会让你恐惧
...what you don't understand.

323
00:30:01,868 --> 00:30:03,233
好了
All right.

324
00:30:10,843 --> 00:30:13,710
我说, 你还挺有种
Yeah, you got spirit, kid. l'll give you that.

325
00:30:13,880 --> 00:30:15,848
比你老子强
More than your old man anyway.

326
00:30:16,015 --> 00:30:20,315
在牢里, 吉尔跟我说了他杀你父母的当晚
ln the joint, Chill told me about the night he killed your parents.

327
00:30:20,486 --> 00:30:22,716
他说你父亲求饶
He said your father begged for mercy.

328
00:30:24,090 --> 00:30:25,819
求饶
Begged.

329
00:30:25,991 --> 00:30:27,390
像条狗一样
Like a dog.

330
00:30:40,239 --> 00:30:42,002
小费给少了?
Should've tipped better.

331
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:53,848
-你要什么? -你的外套
-For what? -Your jacket.

332
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:56,012
行
Okay.

333
00:30:57,123 --> 00:31:00,581
嘿, 给我吧, 这件大衣蛮帅
Hey, hey, hey. Let me have it. lt's a nice coat.

334
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,853
最好别让人看到你穿这件大衣
Be careful who sees you with that.

335
00:31:03,463 --> 00:31:05,363
-他们会来找我的 -谁?
-They're gonna come looking for me. -Who?

336
00:31:05,832 --> 00:31:07,527
所有人
Everyone.

337
00:31:09,836 --> 00:31:11,599
这件...
lt's....

338
00:31:11,771 --> 00:31:13,739
这件大衣蛮帅
lt's a nice coat.

339
00:31:32,057 --> 00:31:36,426
当你和那些罪犯混在一起的时候, 有没有同情他们?
When you lived among the criminals, did you start to pity them?

340
00:31:36,596 --> 00:31:40,293
有, 当我第一次因为饥饿而盗窃的时候
The first time I stole so that I wouldn't starve, yes.

341
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:45,961
我分不清对和错的本质
I lost many assumptions about the simple nature of right and wrong.

342
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,333
当我各处游荡
And when I traveled...

343
00:31:49,509 --> 00:31:52,205
我尝到了犯罪前的恐慌
